<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Environmental Audit Committee Inquiry – Marine Protected Areas</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">the Blue Marine Foundation </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Written evidence from the </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Blue Marine Foundation (BLUE)</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">:  BLUE</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> is a </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">charity and a </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">member of the Marine Reserves Coalition </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> has submitted a </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">high level </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">response to the EA Committee on the points the committee requested.  We do not wish to add to members</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> reading by duplication.  </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">hese are exp</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">anded notes,</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> referred to in paragraph 8 of th</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">main MRC </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">submission, </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">to back up the assertion</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> BLUE has built a public/private partnership </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">in Lyme Bay on the south coast</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">that has made</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> an MPA more successful</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> and indeed given it a vision that initially was absent. We </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">believe</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">that there is </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">potential for many such partnerships in the future.  Indeed, our researches have found </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">an enormous unmet need for more of </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">this way of working around the coast to make MPAs a valued reality.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Lyme Bay</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> - summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">BLUE has discovered in its project in Lyme Bay, a European marine site, that regulation on its own does not make for a successful marine protected area.  It is a necessary and essential part of the picture but there are occasions where the vision and facilitation that can be achieved through co-management on the ground can achieve an even better result, one where the financial and community benefits are tangible to the existing users of the sea and the MPA plays a valued part in community life.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">It has often been overlooked that both European sites and MCZs will continue to be fished, so the fish and shellfish that comes from them, provided it is caught according to the agreed management measures for the site, offers greater reassurance to retailers and to consumer</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> themselves that it is from a sustainably managed source.  It may even be possible in the future to develop a certification scheme that applies to seafood caught from such sites, with the effect of creating demand and value for fishermen’s produce, and building in their support for the area, even where the volumes extracted are lower than they were before.  We would invite the committee to examine the benefits and the constraints of this approach and to ask themselves whether the necessary flexibility of regulation currently exists on the ground.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Lyme Bay background</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Lyme Bay’s rocky reefs are known as</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">”England’s coral garden.”  The </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">reef </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">area is protected as a European marine site for its globally significant flora and fauna</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">- and there is a new MCZ as well as a European SAC</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">.  It is also home to an active fishing community and supports a significant tourism trade. A closure to destructive trawling and dredging was implemented </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">initially </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">across </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">60 </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">q miles of the reefs in 2008, through a statutory instrument.  This ban on mobile gears had the unexpected effect of increasing fishing pressure from </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">pots and set nets to such a degree that it led to unsustainable fishing, economic damage to fishermen’s livelihoods and potentially a threat to the recovery of the protected reef. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Creating a working group</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">In an attempt to solve the problems caused by the closure, BLUE convened informal meetings with fishermen, regulators and conservationists. This was an achievement in itself as these meetings brought together traditionally ‘warring’ parties around the same table and, as a result, together they formed a new body, spanning two IFCA areas, the Lyme Bay Working Group. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Since then (2011) BLUE has been working with the local fishermen to devise a model of self-management which financially benefits and motivates fishing communities to fish in more sustainable ways. </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">This project has been hailed as a “world-first” by Fishing News given its radical collaborative approach involving fishermen in stock management and research.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">….those involved in Lyme Bay fishing have come together with all the bodies involved in seeking to preserve the ecological balance, and </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">they have together drawn up a remarkable voluntary code</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">……Lyme Bay is leading the way.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Oliver Letwin, Conservative MP for West Dorset.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Since its inception project activities and achievements have included:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Creation of a groundbreaking alliance of conservationists, scientists, fishermen and marine authorities in a management committee for the Lyme bay fisheries,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Agreement of a Memorandum of Understanding for the alliance,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Signing up the fishermen’s associations from four ports, Beer, Axmouth /Sidmouth, Lyme Regis and West Bay, to a Code of Practice for fishing in the Lyme Bay protected area,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Development of an initiative to improve </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">ports infrastructure – ice machines and ice containers - to improve </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">catch quality</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> and hence support sustainable fishing through optimising prices,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Creation of a partnership with Seafish to adapt their independently-</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">audited</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> Responsible Fishing Scheme to apply to the inshore fleet of Lyme Bay to further underpin the sustainability, traceability and high quality of catches,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 28.37pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">workshop moderated by BLUE supporters - the Environmental Defense Fund - focused on quality assurance and traceability so that high quality, sustainable seafood from Lyme Bay can be branded and marketed. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Science and ecosystem based management</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Prior to the creation of the reserve there had been no ecosystem based approach to management of the area and there was lack of data documenting the fisheries of Lyme Bay. </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">In order to create an evidence-based management plan for Lyme Bay, the project has put in place significant scientific studies. These will inform the level of fishing effort and other measures required to sustainably manage the fisheries and maintain a balanced ecosystem. Examples of these studies are:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Establishment of The Plymouth University Potting Study, paid for by DEFRA, and delivery of its first monitoring exercise,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Commencement of both a Strategic Environmental Assessment of 38 commercial species and a CEFAS study of the management options for lobster fishing.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Project next steps</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">BLUE is now planning to lead the project through the next stage to ensure a properly planned, well-managed, scientifically-backed, and sustainable fishery. </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">This project will: </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Develop and test a new system to collect fisheries data</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> by the fishermen themselves. This progressive project will supply and install equipment to local fishing boats including a mobile phone app giving real time access to vessel positions (catch traceability) and an exciting new tool for fishermen allowing them to report and sell their catch to buyers whilst still at sea,</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> minimising</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> waste and</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> maximising</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> under</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> utilised</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> species.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Develop a local eco label certification scheme </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">for the premium caught, Lyme Bay seafood. </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Certification will be achieved by meeting criteria under the project's codes, the fitting of </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Inshore Vessel Monitoring Systems (</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">IVMS) and Seafish's Responsible Fishing Scheme certification. Pledges have already been received from fish merchants, Samways, and hotel group, Marriott, that they will buy branded seafood, thus securing a demand and potential price premium.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Communicate the story of this unique marine management project to the wider audience of communities around Lyme Bay through interpretation centres, exhibitions and a schools education outreach programme.</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> The hub of this activity is already in planning for West Bay with smaller exhibitions planned for Lyme Regis, Seaton and Beer.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“It’s a win-win situation for all involved. It’s good for the fish, good for us fisherman, the environment and it shows what a good scheme it is because it’s now going national.”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Alex Jones, Lyme Bay fisherman.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">This project located in England’s very own “coral garden” offers a “win-win-win” for fishermen, conservationists and communities. </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">In short, the fishermen will play an important role in creating a sustainable future for their businesses and benefit from an enhanced market for premium quality, sustainably caught fish; conservationists will benefit from scientific data collected by the fishermen which will act as a foundation for the conservation and protection of sensitive habitats and species both in Lyme Bay and throughout the UK;  and communities will benefit from an enhanced local economy (from both fisheries and tourism). </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Key outcomes will be an improved market for premium</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">“sustainably-caught” Lyme Bay seafood that can be branded and labelled as such, the collection of important scientific data to inform marine planning and importantly</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">establishment of a model project for roll out to other coastal areas in the UK.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Adopting the Lyme Bay model elsewhere in the UK</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">The aim of the Lyme Bay project was always that it would become a blueprint for successful, </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">pragmatic marine conservation. The basic framework of the Lyme Bay model can be applied to any Marine Protected Area (MPA), Special Area of Conservation (SAC) or Marine Conservation Zone (MCZ) around the coast and much of the work done in Lyme Bay can be used in full or in part depending on the nature of the fishery and the marine site. In September 2013 BLUE hosted a conference at the National Sailing Academy in Weymouth attracting 170 delegates. The day was used as an opportunity to share BLUE’s experiences from Lyme as well as offering a platform to fishers, regulators and conservationists from around the UK to discuss challenges and opportunities from their regions. Following on from the conference more than 10 sites around the UK approached BLUE looking for support. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">It is not possible yet to name the areas, as this should remain confidential between them and BLUE until they are comfortable about going public, but this might be possible by the time of the committee’s evidence session.  BLUE is currently carrying out a feasibility study in each of these areas to gain a better understanding of the area, key stakeholders and to identify how and where best to can get involved. In early 2014 BLUE will be shortlisting these candidate sites ready to develop two or three projects in these areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">The key benefits of translating the Lyme model to other areas of the country are: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">The facilitation of a shared vision between different stakeholders, managers, fishermen of several gear types and tourism and community interests.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">The potential to generate additional funding from charity funders to carry out projects that coincide with the management objectives for the area when public funding faces constraints.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">The involvement of retailers in developing brands based on sustainable fishing systems</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> within or adjacent to MPAs</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Summary of </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">possible </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">areas of interest for the inquiry</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Where agreement can be found between communities, as on the Lyme model, is regulation flexible or rapid enough to capitalize on that agreement and rectify agreed problems – given that a consultation for a bylaw takes 18 months?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Are all IFCAs and other regulators open to such public/private partnership arrangements?  Some are less so than others.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-18pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">Are there ways of achieving new MPAs with multiple benefits through this way of working?</span><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt"> We think so.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Effra Light'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">27 January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#00214b; font-family:Cambria; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>